JFrame frame = new JFrame();
frame.setSize(600, 600);
frame.getContentPane().add(new Work());
frame.setLocationRelativeTo(null);
frame.setBackground(Color.LIGHT_GRAY);
frame.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
frame.setVisible(true);

model: classes that deal with databases, data handling classes, back-end, should never reference stuff in view
controller: gets stuff from view events and dumps to models, central communications
view: calls controler when wants to add data to model